        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 6:50PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 649 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm east
of New Lexington, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Crooksville and Eagleport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
